The Herald Andrew Muvishi Mash East Correspondent Zanu-PF Marondera East legislator Patrick Chidakwa has died. Family representative Richard Mavhunga said the legislator died in a South African hospital. Mr Mavhunga said the legislator was diabetic and had a heart ailment. Zanu-PF provincial administrator Tonderai Kwaramba said Marondera district has been robbed a hard worker. “A dark cloud has fallen over Marondera district. We have been robbed of someone special,” he said.